node.text:
Okay so I NEED you to save this right mow and next time you’re working out you’re going to press play and let me take you through this entire lower body follow along warm up segment. 

I’m going to get you ready for your session safely and effectively whether you’re training at home or in the gym I’m literally with you ❗️

SAVE NOW and let me know if you want to see more 👇

node.title: FOLLOW ALONG LOWER BODY ACTIVATION/ WARM UP 🔥

node.text:
Now look.... you might be thinking is all this necessary and my reply is YES. I recently uploaded a full leg day workout on my YouTube to which I showcased a comprehensive lower body dynamic warm up, the warm up took no longer than 5-8mins.

I read a comment that said “I don’t believe you spend this long to warm up it seems excessive” and to which I said “well after 7 years of training I’ve not had one injury nor the clients I’ve trained one on one??”

Moral of the story... you want longevity in your fitness journey. THEN MOBILISE YOUR BODY AND STOP SKIPPING YOUR WARM UPS ❗️❗️

I am a trainer that’s what I love to do train myself and people so whilst I might come off as a little blunt your longevity and well-being means more to me than an extra rep and set you do!

node.title: You want longevity but you’re not willing to spend time to warm up ❗️👀

node.text:
Here in the UK things are opening back up and I want to stress the importance of going at your own pace! 

I designed and built the @toneandsculptapp to be compatible for home or gym. With over 1 million rounds and nearly 1million SCULPT IT! Workouts being completed by women in the comfort of their own homes and bright smiles every single time they smashed a workout I think it’s safe to say the objective is to move your body in a way that feels good to you in a place that feels right for you!

I love the gym but I also love my home workouts in my avocado PJs listening to James brown! Either way do what YOU WANT not what others are doing.

Hope this helps 💙

node.text:
I’m drained.... like I’m truly truly drained today and I’ll tell you why. I am so upset that women still feel that the scales are determining so much of their happiness. I’m so upset that you feel the need to justify your weight in order to show your success when really you should be so proud of everything you have achieved in your journey so far.

I used to HATE myself I used to step on scales every single day (a set of white scales my mum had at home under the bathroom sink) and I used to eat less in order to lose more. 

I now weight nearly 10kg (give or take 22lbs) more than I did when I started my journey and The ONLY numbers I SOMETIMES use to determine longevity of success is maybe being able to lift more over time. 

I want you to SHOW UP FOR YOU! Not for the scales! I want you to try and give me one more rep if you can, one more smile at the end of a workout even if you hate me after a workout I made you do! I want you to be proud of the discipline you’re building and allow that to be your determination of success NOT THE SCALES! 

Trust me I’ve been there! I really really have so I understand you more than you’ll ever believe! 

I’m proud of you for getting this far it’s time you truly start to feel proud of YOU 💙

I might not be Muslim myself but this is absolutely irrelevant because I’m here to help everyone as much as I possible can.

Last year you loved my post on Ramadan so I truly hope this helps! 

I’ll be providing a free “breaking fast” workout on my Facebook at 22nd April 9:15pm GMT COMPLETELY FREE ❗️

Myself and the @toneandsculptapp have put together a comprehensive blog post with our incredible girl @zahara.chowdhury to help you during this special time (on the T&as website now) ❗️

https://toneandsculpt.app/blogs/lifestyle/can-i-exercise-during-ramadan

Introducing one of your KEY exercises for the @toneandsculptapp BEAT YOUR BEST CHALLENGE: the goblet squat 

If you know me you know as your trainer and bestie (bestie first) I have a big BIGA THING about form! It’s literally what I love understanding the most

When I was gaining my personal training qualification I actually wished we was taught more on foundational moves and form executions and would read articles on top of my studies to learn more and more! 

Form is EVERYTHING so please listen, take note and come back to this video whenever you feel confused on how to perfect your goblet squat! 

Send this to a friend who might need help ⭐️

node.text:
I have never believed in anything more than when I started the @toneandsculptapp I remember my initial idea “bringing like minded women to one platform to help them with their fitness journey whilst making friends for life” a place we felt welcomed, loved, celebrated.

Looking back now its insane to think that 142 countries world wide tune in daily to complete their workouts and encourage one another! One of those members is our girl MEL! Mel is one of the youngest T&S users and members. She has been through so much in her life and has found her sense of belongness here with all of us!💙

Some may wonder why I showcase so much of our community and truth is its not that I have to its that I WANT TO CELEBRATE YOU! I have a platform to educates, encourage and push YOU that’s what ill always be here for!

I found out is was Mens B day from our @toneandsculptapp Ambassadors and well… the rest is history.

I love and adore you Mel! You are truly a shining star. @mellghewitt

node.title: THIS IS WHY I LOVE BEING YOUR TRAINER 💙

LANDMINE SQUAT HACK ❗️

This will CHANGE your life and look im not exaggerating and I truly truly would say if I have but I spent a whole gym session figuring out how to help you set up your LANDMINE squats and I couldn’t find proper tips anywhere! I messed around a little and boom it came to me! Use a bench to ease the load and pressure. (If this tips been done before apologises in advanced I would credit the relevant creator 💙) 

I truly hope this helps! Let me know if you try this or if you find it helpful! 💙

node.text:
3 TIPS TO HELP IMPROVE YOUR PULL DOWNS! 

LIKE 💙 now to refer to another time and show support

To all my @toneandsculptapp strong program community I need you to pay attention to my form in this video! This exercise is a staple on your pull days and it requires a lot of form check to ensure your perfecting it ⭐️ if you’re yet to join our global community the link is in the bio to come sign up for free ❗️

TIPS:

✅ Thumbs out: this avoids stress added to the forearms. Remember biceps and forearms are naturally activated when training you back so your grip makes a difference 

✅ Lean slightly back and bring your chest upright! That doesn’t mean you lean completely back! So find a happy medium 

✅ Pull down with elbows and create a semi circle! This will help you contract your back more to move with motion

Did you find this post helpful if so leave a comment below or tag a friend who might find this helpful too 👇

LOWER BACK PAIN ❗️

Leave a LIKE 💙 if you find this post helpful and to support 

If you’re suffering from lower back pain when performing the leg press machine I need you to give these three simple tips ago on your next leg day

✅ Place your feet higher 
✅ Rotate feet outwards 
✅ Push core into spine and bum down
✅ Knee to Shoulder to ensure no caving! 

I truly hope these tips help!

DAILY PRE WORKOUT ROUTINE ✨

Have you tried having a pre workout routine ? If not I am BEGGGGING YOU to try this! 

✅ Pick your go to pump song! If you know me you know Lizzo is my life
✅ Choose a cute outfit ! 
✅ Pre workout I’m drinking @womensbest ENERGY DRINK now available to purchase now via the website in raspberry grape flavour 🍇 
✅ Smash your session ⭐️

Point is, if you start treating your workouts as a chore you’ll dread it! If you start seeing your workouts as an event, you’ll look forward to it! 

COMMENT A ⭐️ BELOW NOW if you’re going to try this routine 👇 promise it will help you

node.text:
This didn’t take me 5 months it took me 5 years and then ✨

So how did I keep going ? Well I stopped viewing fitness as a chore I’d tick off my to do list and instead I started to see it as a tool that helped better my life, mentally and physically. 

I cannot even begin to tell you how the girl on the left felt mentally. Bestie, I was not the woman I am today. I got cheated on and felt like I was not good enough, I didn’t deserve love, I didn’t deserve to be happy! I felt sorry for myself daily, it was draining emotionally and physically. 

Working out has elevated my life completely! It started off as me trying to change myself and now I just want to better myself DAILY!

That’s why I created the @toneandsculptapp because it is based on longevity, helping you build consistency and confidence. It is not a quick fit! It is not something you do in a week! It is not something that will guarantee results (sorry but we just don’t do that here)❗️plus having a global community makes your journey even more enjoyable as you never feel alone 💙

I created it because I wanted to show women how it’s so important to have a structure! To eat! To be consistent! And to understand that you will have bad days!

I have weight trained for longer than 5 years, I do not cut out specific food groups! I do not deprive myself! Pleaseeeee stop thinking you have to in order to see results! I literally beg you! 

PS yes I’ve lost my boobies but I’ve gained a whole lot of assssss 🤣 win some lose some ayyyyy

node.text:
Why is it so hard to just start?

I find that starting something new is the biggest challenge anyone can take. Starting something new means you’ve consciously told yourself you want to make a change and change is scary. 

Change requires us to get uncomfortable. It means we will feel uncertainty of what the future will hold or it will even make us wonder if the change was “worth it” 

But I want you to close your eyes and imagine all the right things that could happen with starting something new, imagine the positive change and self growth. That’s enough for you to just START. 

I feel like sometimes we spend so much of our valuable time and energy dwelling on whether something will work or not that we lose sight on why we wanted the change in the first place, why we are so desperate to start something new and why we have daily internal conversations with ourselves debating whether to do it or not! 

If you’re reading this today I just want you to go for it and not look back, just take the chance and make it happen because nothing is more rewarding than knowing you just gave it ago and did your best.

node.text:
Forever trying to find that healthy work/ life balance as I’m someone who would rather be working all day than do anything society deems as “fun” but I recently spoke to my mumma and she said “krissy you tell people not to do anything that isn’t sustainable so why don’t you listen to your own advice” 

Making it a priority to actually not touch work or feel bad about it on weekend! Actually being present with the people I love and myself instead of thinking about the next five moves. 

I know I talk a lot about wellness but as I’ve always said… if I can’t practice it myself how can I possible “preach it” 

Your girls going to get some yummy food watch a movie, eat my fav snacks and be around people I adore. 

So if you’re working overtime, studying, really overthinking about the future please do me a favour and switch off for a little…. It will all fall into place bestie I promise 💙
